        <!-- div semantic section for content -->
        <div class="card-1">
            <h2>Articles on the Future of Computer Graphics from Siggraph</h2>
                <article>
                <h3><a href="https://blog.siggraph.org/2025/10/making-scientific-discoveries-accessible-to-everyone.html/" target="_blank"><u>Making Scientific Discoveries Accessible to Everyone</u></a></h3>
                <p>
                    Specialists at NASA are working to make visual scientific data more engaging with general population. By doing so they are converting raw sattelite-model data
                    into visualizations using graphical tools such as Houdini, Maya and custom graphical piplining. The underlying problem is that the visualizations are large-scaled reaching 
                    issues with computational power and decisions for how much data can be shown.
                </p>
                </article>

                <article>
                <h3><a href="https://blog.siggraph.org/2025/08/generative-ai-in-computer-graphics-navigating-the-challenges-and-seizing-the-opportunities.html/" target="_blank"><u>Generative AI in Computer Graphics</u></a></h3>
                <p>
                    An opinionated article addressing the changes in computer graphics workflow. Discusses the opportunities and challenges many industry studios face. The article tackles the rise of generative AI
                    noting that it allows artists to experiment with ideas much quicker than in the past. It mentions the computational problems and randomness of generated content, mentioning that artists are looking
                    for consistent feedback. Raises the question of how AI can maintain scalability, consistency and collaborative workflows.
                </p>
                </article>

                <article>
                <h3><a href="https://blog.siggraph.org/2025/07/will-ai-completely-take-over-computer-graphics.html/" target="_blank"><u>Will AI Completely Take Over Computer Graphics?</u></a></h3>
                <p>
                    The article tackles the question on whether AI will completely transform and take over the Computer Graphics field. It discusses the overall adoption of AI within computer graphics
                    pipelines and how it is taking over ever aspect from hardware processing, APIs, application and Tools. Briefly discussing the investment in AI for future graphics systems.
                    It further mentions the ethical concerns of AI on job security to the decrease of human involvement in production. 
                </p>
                </article>
